      {
        "metric": "One-line verdict: The M113 is one of Mercedes' most durable V8s — age-related oil leaks and ignition wear are its main weaknesses — buy on maintenance history, not mileage.",
        "value": "Best for: Buyers wanting a bulletproof V8 Mercedes with reasonable running costs for the era."
      },
      {
        "metric": "Avoid if: You can't budget for proactive gasket and ignition system maintenance.",
        "value": "Supporting Evidence"
      },
      {
        "metric": "The M113 (and its supercharged M113K sibling) is widely regarded as one of the most reliable and durable powerplants ever produced by Mercedes-Benz. Found across a huge range of models from the late 1990s to the mid-2000s, this V8 established Mercedes-Benz's reputation for bulletproof V8 engineering.",
        "value": "The engine's durability stems from deliberate engineering choices: Mercedes avoided aggressive, unproven solutions and instead refined proven ideas to a very high standard. Its SOHC three-valve-per-cylinder design with duplex roller timing chain, aluminium block and heads, and conservative tuning that delivers torque low in the rev range all contribute to exceptional longevity."
      },
      {
        "metric": "Key strengths:",
        "value": "* Exceptional longevity — many examples have passed 200,000 miles without internal rebuilds"
      },
      {
        "metric": "* Aluminium construction — lightweight block and heads with forged steel connecting rods",
        "value": "* Conservative engineering — SOHC, 3 valves per cylinder, duplex timing chain"
      },
      {
        "metric": "* Twin spark ignition — improves combustion stability and reduces emissions",
        "value": "* Proven 5G-Tronic automatic transmission — robust and well-matched to the engine"
      },
      {
        "metric": "Known age-related issues:",
        "value": "* Oil leaks — valve cover gaskets, breather covers, rear main seal"
      },
      {
        "metric": "* Ignition system — worn spark plugs, failing ignition coils",
        "value": "* Harmonic balancer failure — rubber element separating from metal"
      },
      {
        "metric": "* Cooling system — water pump, thermostat, radiator leaks",
        "value": "* Timing chain tensioner — rattling on startup indicates tensioner wear"
      },
